        <body>       

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>151 East 73<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> St<lb/>
                New York Oct 29. 1886<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Your welcome<lb/> favor duly received&#45;&#45;as you will<lb/> no doubt have heard all that was<lb/> done at our meeting&#44; from Mr Hyneman<lb/> who was present&#44; I will not go<lb/> into any repetition of same&#45;&#45;<lb/> I think we are now in a fair way<lb/> to make an early and actual start<lb/> with the Seminary&#44; and only by so<lb/> doing&#44; and showing that we are in<lb/> earnest and mean business&#44; can we<lb/> get the confidence and support of<lb/> our coreligionists all over the country&#45;&#45;<lb/> I have entire faith that our efforts<lb/> will be endorsed and sustained by the<lb/> Jews of the U. S&#44; who believe that the<lb/> vital consideration for our future<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>maintenance of Judaism&#44; is in the proper<lb/> Educaiton of our Teachers &#38; Rabbis&#45;&#45;<lb/> An address has been &#91;&#63;&#93;opsed&#44; and<lb/> will be issued&#44; and everything done<lb/> to place the importance of the matter<lb/> properly before the Jews of America&#45;&#45;<lb/>  As to farther details&#44; and much else<lb/> affecting the interests of the Seminary&#44;<lb/> I shall be glad to confer with you<lb/> when you visit this city&#45;&#45;If<lb/> possible&#44; let me know when you<lb/> are coming&#44; so that I shall <hi rend="underline">surely</hi><lb/> meet you&#45;&#45;I have spoken to Mr<lb/> Cowen&#44; and we will try to get the<lb/> Madison Ave Synagogue into our<lb/> Seminary fold&#45;&#45;Dr Lasker&#39;s Con&#45;<lb/>gregation in Boston has made<lb/> application to join&#45;&#45;others will<lb/> do the same&#44; when properly seen &#38;<lb/> talked to&#45;&#45;assuring you that I<lb/> am fully impressed with the weight<lb/> and responsibility of our undertaking<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>and that I am heart and soul<lb/> in the good work&#44; for which<lb/> you have labored and thought so<lb/> long and so earnestly&#44; and looking<lb/> to you mainly for advise and<lb/> counsel to bring it to a happy<lb/> and blessed conclusion<lb/></p>
            <p>I am sincerely yours<lb/>
                Joseph Blumenthal<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
